
Overview of noun hesitation

The noun hesitation has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (4) hesitation, vacillation, wavering -- (indecision in speech or action)
2. (2) reluctance, hesitancy, hesitation, disinclination, indisposition -- (a certain degree of unwillingness; "a reluctance to commit himself"; "his hesitancy revealed his basic indisposition"; "after some hesitation he agreed")
3. (1) hesitation, waver, falter, faltering -- (the act of pausing uncertainly; "there was a hesitation in his speech")
